race.description: Ross Granata Motors - Tab Venue Mode Handicap
race.comment: CROWN LEGEND (5) came with a powerful run from back in the field to register an impressive win over 1300m at Gunnedah two runs back. Found a Rosehill Highway over 1500m too tough last start. Back in his right race today and despite a wide draw looks the one to beat. COMMANDO JACK (12) has hit form at his last couple. Contested a similar race to this two starts ago and was beaten under a length after leading most of the way. Races well here with two wins and a placing from four visits. Genuine contender. A BOY NAMED SOO (14) surprised a few when he scored convincingly first-up over 1200m at Dubbo. Takes on a better field today but he drops a kilo, draws a nice gate, and has decent stats at this longer journey. WASTED DAYS (1) was never in the hunt in a Randwick Highway last start after an easy win at Parkes the run prior. New to this trip but should give a good account. TO BE FRANK (2) is fitter for two runs back from a spell and is down in grade on the latest outing.
